question.title: PrivilegedActionException only on linux jenkins builds

node.contents: Recently I set up a few debian slaves for our jenkins server. I have been slowly working through various bugs related to platform dependence, and have had a fair amount of luck getting things working correctly cross platform. While most of it is just typical file operations, one of the strange issues I see, seems to be related to the OS the unit tests are running on, but only when using maven builds on jenkins.

node.contents: The problem is that when I run these test on linux or windows as a JUnit test through eclipse, they pass 100% of the time. When I run them on linux or windows as a maven run unit test,they also pass, but when they are run as maven unit test on our jenkins server, and only on the linux platforms we receive exceptions like this:

node.contents: But they yeild the same results. While I've petitioned to remove these types of unit tests from our test classes, as I feel they are a testing anti-pattern, used only to satisfy minimum code coverage requirements, rather than to write legitmate unit tests, I would still like to know why they only fail while running via jenkins linux slaves. So the question is, why do these unit tests fail on jenkins linux slaves and no place else?
